<TITLE> Azizul stresses 'financial power' for women </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 20 (bdnews24.com)Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam has said no nation can grow economically until its women are financially empowered. The adviser Wednesday launched "Designs on Diversification", a Bangladesh Women Chamber of Commerce and Industry project, funded by the European Union. In his speech as chief guest, the adviser stressed the need for empowering women to boost the country's economy. "For instance, Bangladesh's readymade garments industry is largely dependent on women," the adviser said. Azizul referred to the government's steps to encourage women entrepreneurship. "The government in the last budget increased spending on women-related issues to 25 percent from 22 percent," Azizul said. He also pointed to the government's initiative to set up the SME (Small and Medium Enterprises) Foundation focused mainly on women entrepreneurs. The adviser called on lendersboth banks and non-bank financial institutionsto pay special attention to woman entrepreneurs. "Women will be the best loan clients for banks. We all know the success rate of credit recovery from rural women under microcredit programmes," he said. Azizul however said Bangladesh has to go a long way in the realm of empowering women. In her welcome address, BWCCI president Selima Ahmed thanked the partners of the project, Birmingham Chamber of Commerce and Industry, Lyon Chamber of Commerce and Silk Association of Nepal. bdn
